.row.sign_up_css
  .span5
    %h1 Why Help Startups?
    %h4 1) Awesome stories to tell your friends.
    %p "You will not beleive how excited the founder got when I showed the sales team how to close a sale... "
    %h4 
      2) You heard about that 
      = link_to "graffiti artist.", "http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2095385/Facebook-IPO-Graffiti-artist-David-Choe-painted-HQ-set-bumper-shares-payday.html" , :target => "_blank"
    %p "David Choe, 35, was asked to paint the offices in Palo Alto, California, in 2005, and was offered the choice by then-president Sean Parker of being paid a few thousand cash or the equivalent in shares."
    %h4 3) Because they need you.
    %p Startups are hard.  Founders have to learn everything from scratch and they need the help of great people who have been there before and have great skills.  If you have aquired skills that you think could help founders, startups would love to meet you.

  .span6.offset1
    .well{:style => "padding: 50px 0 30px 120px;"}
      %div{:style => "padding: 0px 0 10px 40px;"}
        %h3 Apply Now
      = simple_form_for(resource, :as => resource_name, :url => registration_path(resource_name),  html: {class: 'form-horizontal'}) do |f|
        = devise_error_messages!
        = f.input :name, label: "Your Name"
        = f.input :linked_in, label: "Linked In URL"
        = f.input :bio, as: :text, input_html: {rows: "6"}
        = f.input :email
        = f.input :password
        = f.input :password_confirmation
        %div{:style => "padding: 60px 0 0 10px;"}
          = f.submit "Submit Application", class: "btn btn-warning btn-large"
    /* = render "devise/shared/links" */